definitions.definition: To recover consciousness after fainting etc.
definitions.example: She came to with the aid of smelling salts.

definitions.definition: To stop a sailing vessel, especially by turning into the wind. See also come about.

definitions.example: so how much does that come to?;  the bill comes to £10 each
come to an end;  come to a conclusion;  come to an agreement;  come to a halt

definitions.definition: To devote attention to in due course; to come around to.
definitions.example: I'll come to your question in a minute.

definitions.definition: To befall; to happen to; to come upon.
definitions.example: I pray no harm will come to you.

definitions.definition: (usually in present tense) To regard or specifically pertain to.
definitions.example: He's the best when it comes to detective fiction.
